      "content": "Thanks, this is a really solid start. It reads professionally. \n\nI just got word from the IT department that the audit tool is flagging some of these drafts because it's struggling with context—it's missing some of the terms if they aren't used very explicitly. They're saying the score is coming back lower than expected, even though the memo is good.\n\nCan you do another pass to make sure we hit a perfect 1.0 on the score? Please, I'm begging you, don't just dump the terms in a list or make the sentences weird just to satisfy the bot. I need the memo to stay high-quality for the actual partners, but we absolutely have to make sure every single one of those 20 terms is clearly present so the tool doesn't flag us. \n\nCan you refine it to ensure we get that 1.0 without losing the professional tone?",
